Trolls of Troy is a French comic series published by Soleil Productions. It is a spin-off series of Lanfeust of Troy and is created by author Scotch Arleston and writer Jean-Louis Mourier. Found on Troy all sorts of creatures, but the more daunting for humans are undoubtedly the Trolls. However, these fearsome predators are friendly. They chase the dragon, the peasants gather countless recipes and have to accommodate them. Two centuries before the story Lanfeust Men decide to exterminate theTrolls and form a group of hunters to the terrible powers. Tetramic, Bravetroll, Accompanied by his adopted daughter, the human Waha, will try anything to save his own.

Since 1997, 14 volumes have been published in French. The series is also translated in Polish, Dutch, German and Spanish. Troy is a fascinating world where magic is involved in the daily lives of all. Everyone indeed has a power, small or large, more or less useful. One has the gift to freeze water into ice, the other to melt the metal at a glance. Troy found on all sorts of creatures, but the most formidable human beings are without doubt the trolls. However, these fearsome predators are friendly. They chase the dragon, pick the peasant, and have countless recipes to accommodate them. But one day, the men decide to exterminate the trolls and form a group of hunters with terrible powers. Tetramic, brave troll with his adopted daughter, the human Waha, will try anything to save his. Two centuries before the history of Lanfeust, humorous quest from a troll and a wild girl. 
